medications.name: Sertraline
medications.response: Poor (Symptoms persist after 4 weeks of treatment)

changes_made.rationale: Inadequate clinical response (persistent symptoms including anhedonia, early morning awakening, and suicidal ideation) after 4 weeks at 50mg. Dose titrated to 100mg daily to reach therapeutic level.

peer_review_finding.details: *Sertraline* is a standard SSRI agent appropriate for the proposed diagnosis of **Recurrent Major Depressive Disorder (F33.1)**. No significant mismatch flagged.
